      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>One of the two homilies on Melchizedek's origin attributed to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3255CyrilI">Cyril I</persName>. Both homilies according to  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/TQ2NBVAC"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia"/><title level="m">Chrestomathia Aethiopica edita et glossario explanata</title><editor><forename>August</forename><surname>Dillmann</surname></editor><pubPlace>Lipsiae</pubPlace><publisher>T. O. Weigel</publisher><date>1866</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_V2XoxZmczckC</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Literature</note><note type="tag">bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Literature</note><note type="tag">bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia</note></bibl> were translated from the Greek,
               but the original is lost and the Ethiopic version is the only known one, see
                     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/4TZ6V4PR"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:CPG3"/><title level="m">Clavis patrum Graecorum, III: A Cyrillo Alexandrino ad Iohannem Damascenum</title><title type="short">CPG</title><title level="s">Corpus Christianorum</title><author><forename>Maurice</forename><surname>Geerard</surname></author><pubPlace>Turnhout</pubPlace><publisher>Brepols</publisher><date>1979</date><series><title level="s">Corpus Christianorum</title></series><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:CPG3</note></note><note type="tag">bm:CPG3</note></bibl>. Its Gǝʿǝz version known to be transmitted as
               part of <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3309Qerellos">Qerǝllos</title> or along the <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2365Storyo">Story of Melchizedek</title> .
            </p>
